unt archives and create cinematic arenas for witnessing Black women battling for survival during pivotal and exceedingly violent moments in US history.Duke University Press Scholars of Color First Book Award recipient  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 05. Dez 2022) 0aAfrican American feminists. 0aAfrican American women motion picture producers and directors. 0aExperimental filmszUnited States. 0aFeminism and motion pictureszUnited States. 0aFeminist film criticism. 0aWomanismzUnited States. 0aWomen, Black, in motion pictures. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / African American Studies.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478023791?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478023791423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478023791/original  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles